Field Detail

identifier

public java.lang.String identifier
Criteria Identifier. This identifier allows saved filters to be reloaded.

e.g "duedate"

text

public java.lang.String text
Criteria Title. If the title contains ?, this is replaced by the entry label string selected.

e.g "Due: ?"

sql

public java.lang.String sql
Criterion SQL. This query should return task id's. If this contains ?, it will be replaced by the entry value

Examples:

  • SELECT _id FROM tasks WHERE dueDate <= ?
  • SELECT task FROM metadata WHERE value = '?'

valuesForNewTasks

public ContentValues valuesForNewTasks
Values to apply to a task when quick-adding a task from a filter created from this criterion. ? will be replaced with the entry value. For example, when a user views tasks tagged 'ABC', the tasks they create should also be tagged 'ABC'. If set to null, no additional values will be stored for a task.

public java.lang.String[] entryTitles
Array of entries for user to select from

icon

public Bitmap icon
Icon for this criteria. Can be null for no bitmap

name

public java.lang.String name
Criteria name. This is displayed when users are selecting a criteria
